        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/5–2446</note>
                <head>No. 397<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Briefing Book Paper</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d397fn1">For the full text
                            of this briefing paper, see attachment 1 to <ref target="#d513">document
                                No. 513</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">East Prussia</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">a.</hi>
                    </label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Recommendation:</hi>—East Prussia (except for the
                        Koenigsberg district, which presumably will go to the Soviet Union) should
                        be ceded to Poland.</item>
                    <label>
                        <hi rend="italic">b.</hi>
                    </label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Basic Data:</hi>— …</item>
                    <label/>
                    <item>… The whole of East Prussia is claimed by the Warsaw Polish Government.
                        The Soviet Union favors Polish acquisition of East Prussia or all of the
                        province except for the northeastern sector, including the chief city and
                        part [<hi rend="italic">port</hi>] of Koenigsberg which it intends to annex.
                        … </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-30">June 30,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
